sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects a suspicious svchost process start
It is extremely abnormal for svchost.exe to spawn without any CLI arguments and is normally observed when a malicious process spawns the process and injects code into the process memory space.

mitre_attack_techniques.signature_description: link function at runtime on Windows
Creates COM task schedule object (often to register a task for autostart)
Hijacks the control flow in another process
May sleep (evasive loops) to hinder dynamic analysis
PE file has an executable .text section which is very likely to contain packed code (zlib compression ratio < 0.3)
PE file has section (not .text) which is very likely to contain packed code (zlib compression ratio < 0.011)
Overwrites code with unconditional jumps - possibly settings hooks in foreign process
Tries to detect virtualization through RDTSC time measurements
Tries to detect virtualization through RDTSC time measurements
C2 URLs / IPs found in malware configuration
